==Demographics==
[[File:Seltzer Hose Co, Norwegian Twp, Schuylkill Co PA.JPG|right|thumb|Seltzer Hose Co.]]
The total population in 2010 was 296 according to the [[United States Census Bureau|U.S. Census Bureau]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=&g=1600000US4269256&table=S0101&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S0101&hidePreview=false&vintage=2010&cid=DP05_0001E&layer=place&lastDisplayedRow=23&mode=|website=data.census.gov|access-date=2020-01-22|title=Explore Census Data }}</ref> in this [[Census-designated place|Census Designated Place]] (CDP). The racial makeup of the CDP was 100.00% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]].

There were 86.2 males per 100 females (137 male, 159 female). The age breakdown shows 35 children under 15 years of age, 47 between ages 15–19, 7 aged 20–34, 124 aged 35–54, 83 aged 55 and older.

20.7% of the population aged 15 and older has never married. 55.6% are now married (in 2010). 9.2% are divorced or separated. 14.6% are widowed. 72.9% of the population 25 years of age or older in the CDP have graduated from high school or attended college, including 11.6% with a graduate or professional degree. The median income per capita (15 years of age and older) was $16,042. 14.9% of the population is living below the [[Poverty threshold|poverty line]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=&g=1600000US4269256&table=S0601&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S0601&hidePreview=false&vintage=2010&cid=DP05_0001E&layer=place&lastDisplayedRow=51&mode=|website=data.census.gov|access-date=2020-01-22|title=Explore Census Data }}</ref>

Data from the 2010 American Community Survey conducted by the Census Bureau indicates that there were 127 households in the CDP with 78 total families.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=&g=1600000US4269256&table=S1101&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101&hidePreview=false&vintage=2010&cid=DP05_0001E&layer=place&lastDisplayedRow=26&mode=|website=data.census.gov|access-date=2020-01-22|title=Explore Census Data }}</ref>

The median income for a household in the CDP was $48,681.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=&g=1600000US4269256&table=S2503&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S2503&hidePreview=false&vintage=2010&cid=DP05_0001E&layer=place&lastDisplayedRow=56&mode=|website=data.census.gov|access-date=2020-01-22|title=Explore Census Data }}</ref>

